## Page Templates

### Simple HTML Template
Define function that converts a template using settings

```
function render_template($template, $settings) {
    $text = file_get_contents($template);
    $text = transform_text($text, $settings);
    return $text;
}
```


### Simple HTML Template
Define function that converts text using settings

```
function transform_text ($text, $settings) {
    foreach ($settings as $key => $value) {
        $text = str_replace("{{ $key }}",  $value,  $text);
    }
    return $text;
}
```


### Simple HTML Template
Define settings to replace chunks of text

```
$settings = article_settings("Gettysburg Address",
    "Four score and seven years ago ...",  "Abe Lincoln");

render_template("article.html", $settings)

<h3>Gettysburg Address</h3>
<p>Four score and seven years ago ...</p>
```


### Read Page Template
Define a page template with spot for settings

```
$text = file_get_contents("page.html");

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
    <head>

        <meta charset="UTF-8">
        <title>{{ page_title }}</title>

        <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">

    </head>
    <body>

        <header>
            <img src="Bear.png" alt="Bear Logo"/>
            <h1>{{ site_title }}</h1>
            <h2>{{ page_title }}</h2>
        </header>
        <main>

            {{ content }}

        </main>
    </body>
</html>
```


### Page Template
Define settings to replace chunks of text

```
$settings = array("page_title" => "Page Templates",
                  "site_title" => "BACS 200 Demos");

$text = render_template("page.html", $settings);

```


### Page Template
Render page using fixed page template and settings

```
function render_page($content) {
    return render_template("page.html", $content));
}

render_page($settings);
```


